<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880712-0036 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Home Federal Savings andamp; Loan Association </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HFD </CO><TEXT>   Home Federal Savings andamp; Loan Association said it will ask shareholders to approve the formation of a holding company for the San Diego thrift at a special shareholder meeting Aug. 12.    The holding company, to be named HomeFed Corp., will be incorporated under Delaware law, the company said. &quot;Reorganization as a holding company will allow us more strategic and financial flexibility,&quot; Kim Fletcher, Home Federal chairman and chief executive officer, said.    Home Federal, with more than $15 billion in assets, is the nation's tenth largest thrift. </TEXT></DOC>